The paper proposes an incremental learning framework based on neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The use of a grow-and-prune paradigm to update the network architecture suggests a focus on neural network optimization, which is often discussed in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories. The application of the framework to image and speech recognition tasks suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
